

HTML Summary Report

What is HTML?
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language for creating web pages.

Structure of HTML
HTML pages have a basic structure: `<!DOCTYPE>`, `<html>`, `<head>`, and `<body>`.

Steps to Create an HTML Page
Start with `<!DOCTYPE html>`, then add `<html>`, with `<head>` for metadata and `<body>` for content.

Doctype Declaration
`<!DOCTYPE html>` tells the browser you're using HTML5.

Head Tag
The `<head>` contains the title, styles, and other metadata.

Paragraph Tag 
`<p>` defines paragraphs of text.

Image Tag 
`<img>` embeds images using the `src` attribute.

Line Break (`<br>`) Tag 
Inserts a line break in text.

Text Style
Use tags like `<b>`, `<i>`, and `<strong>` for styling text.

Horizontal Line (`<hr>`) Tag 
Creates a horizontal line across the page.

Link
`<a href="">` creates hyperlinks to other pages.

Lists
Use `<ul>` for unordered and `<ol>` for ordered lists.

Div Tag
`<div>` groups content for styling and layout.

Forms 
`<form>` collects user input with `<input>`, `<label>`, etc.

Tables
Use `<table>`, `<tr>`, and `<td>` to display tabular data.

Blog
Combine HTML elements to structure a blog layout (e.g., using `<article>`, `<section>`).

